		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ah, that makes perfect sense. And yes you're right, historically protestantism came along a bit later, shortly followed by the subfaction calvinism. The struggle in wallachia at this point is largely between Orthodoxism (majority) and catholicism, with judaism as a recognized minority. <br /><br />In addition, Wallachia was yet a moderately independent protectorate of the Ottoman Empire (the correct term is Suzerainty (effectively mening semisovereign)).<br /><br />The Belmonts, however, have their family line continued into times of protestantism.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


